Most (34) of the 40 Critically Endangered coastal ecosystem types are within the coastal portion of the terrestrial realm (@fig-etsmap, @fig-etsgraph, @tbl-etsnumbers), with a slightly higher proportion of types and extent among semi-coastal vegetation types (44% of types; 17.8% of extent) than coastal vegetation types (38% of types; 10.4% of extent). This is because pressures on land act more locally and intensively than they do in the aquatic realms, often causing complete habitat loss (e.g., houses replacing grasslands) rather than degrees of degradation (e.g., different pollution levels in estuaries).

Because the data and/or assessment methodologies have changed in the realm assessments since the NBA 2018, the results are not comparable between the two assessments. However, the latest results do show that the South African coastal zone is more threatened than was previously reported.


